application_type_full: Prior Approval: Change of use - offices to dwellinghouses
description:
Prior Approval application in relation to the following considerations arising from the change of use of the building of floors 1 to 4 and 6 to 12 to residential use (C3) use class creating 141 residential units:  
a)	transport and highways impacts of the development
b)	contamination risks on the site; and
c)	flooding risks on the site.
decision_conditions:
1. INFORMATIVE : This decision does not provide a lawful development certificate or in any other way confirm as lawful the change of use of the building to residential use under Class J of Part 3 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (Amendment) (England) Order 2013.

The decision is limited to the assessment and acceptability or otherwise of the prior approval application submitted under section J.2 of Class J of Part 3 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (Amendment) (England) Order 2013.  

The applicant is advised to submit a Certificate of Lawful Development application (proposed development) with supporting evidence to confirm the change of use as permitted under Class J of Part 3 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (Amendment) (England) Order 2013 complying with the exceptions of section J.1 of the class.  An application fee of £385 per residential dwelling created (equivalent to planning application for creation of residential dwellings) would also be required.

In the absence of a Lawful Development Certificate and Prior Approval consent the Council reserves the right to take Enforcement Action against any change of use of the building which is not lawful.  This for instance may include the change of use of the building to residential use where failing to comply with the provisions of Class J of Part 3 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (Amendment) (England) Order 2013.

Details on how to apply for a Certificate of Lawful Development (proposed development) can be found on the Council website at the below weblink:

http://www.islington.gov.uk/services/planning/planninginisl/plan_apply/application_forms/Pages/default.aspx
